definitions.definition: ( chiefly in the plural , often with "the" ) A state of nervousness .
examples: That creepy movie gave me the jitters .

definitions.definition: ( telecommunications ) An abrupt and unwanted variation of one or more signal characteristics .
( data visualization ) A random positioning of data points to avoid visual overlap.

secondary_definitions: ( chiefly in the plural , often with "the" ) A state of nervousness .
( telecommunications ) An abrupt and unwanted variation of one or more signal characteristics .
( data visualization ) A random positioning of data points to avoid visual overlap.

definitions.definition: A program or routine that performs jitting ; a just-in-time compiler .

main_definition: ( computing ) A program or routine that performs jitting ; a just-in-time compiler .
